Class ItemImage

java.lang.Object
com.example.omninventory.ItemImage
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class ItemImage extends Object implements Serializable
Encapsulates functionality related to an image attached to an item; the URI, path in storage and/or on system, etc.

    • equalRef

      public boolean equalRef(@Nullable ItemImage image)
      Checks if the storagePaths of two images are both non-null and equal. This is useful for checking if two images refer to the same image in Firebase Storage.
      Parameters:
      image - ItemImage to compare with this ItemImage.
      Returns:
      boolean, 'true' if ItemImages both non-null and refer to same image in Firebase storage, 'false' otherwise.

    • getNeededRotation

      public int getNeededRotation()
      Reads image EXIF data from a filePath (this is only applicable if image stored locally in filesystem by app; i.e. if image was taken using EditActivity's feature for taking images). If this does apply, and filePath has been set properly, this method reads the EXIF data and returns the degrees by which the image should be rotated in order to display it properly.
      Returns:
      Integer number of degrees to rotate image; either 0, 90, 180, or 270. Returns 0 if an error occurs.

    • fixRotation

      public void fixRotation(android.content.Context context)
      If the image represented by this ItemImage is stored in the local filesystem accessible by the app (i.e. if image was taken using EditActivity's feature for taking images), this method obtains the necessary EXIF information to correctly rotate it, rotates it, and then writes the correctly-rotated image bitmap to the same file location. This is useful because rotating the image in-app allows us to display it properly, but it also needs to be rotated in-filesystem if we want it to upload to Firebase Storage with the correct rotation.
      Parameters:
      context - Context from which this method called.
